text:
\begin{equation}\label{eq:evidence}
E_n =  p\left( [ \right) d {\operatorname{|}} M_n] = \int_\Theta  p\left( [ \right) d {\operatorname{|}} \Theta, M_n]  p\left( [ \right) \Theta {\operatorname{|}} M_n] d\Theta \,. 
\end{equation}

\begin{align}
   p\left( [ \right) d {\operatorname{|}} \Theta, M_n] = \left(2\pi\right)^{-N/2} &
                             \left[ \prod_{i=1}^N \left(\sigma_i^2 + s^2\right)^{-1/2} \right] \times \nonumber \\ 
                           & \times \exp \left \{ - \sum_{i=1}^N \frac{\left[ v_i - V_0 - V_n\,(t_i, \theta) \right]^2}{2\left(\sigma_i^2 + s^2\right)} \right\}
\end{align}

\begin{equation}\label{eq:odds}
	\mathcal{O}_{ij} = \frac{ p\left( [ \right) M_i {\operatorname{|}} d]}{p\,(M_j {\operatorname{|}} d)} = \frac{ p\left( [ \right) M_i]}{p\,(M_j)} \cdot \frac{ p\left( [ \right) d {\operatorname{|}} M_i]}{p\,(d {\operatorname{|}} M_j)}
\end{equation}

nexttext:
The preferred model, when using these criteria, is the one which gives the lowest AIC$_C$ and BIC values. 
For the choice of one model to be significant one can require differences $\Delta$AIC$_C$ and $\Delta$BIC around 10 \citep{Burnham2010}.




